primaryHost.about:
We have lived in various neighborhoods in Brooklyn for the past 17 years (David was here from birth), but we found our dream home in Bed-Stuy.  I am originally from Kansas and started traveling internationally in high school.  I studied abroad in Spain as well as in Italy in college, and after we had kids about 15 years ago, I needed to be sure that international travel could still be a part of our lives, so we went to Mexico when our daughter was 4 months old, and I took her to London at 12 months with my sister.  

Since then, we have traveled around Switzerland, London, Denmark, Sicily, Mexico, Belize, Honduras, Canada, Croatia, Singapore, Vietnam, and Thailand, among other trips stateside.  Our last big trips were sailing in Croatia and hiking in the Swiss Alps and scuba diving in Roatan, Honduras (the kids were certified as Junior divers  a couple years ago). We hope to continue our adventures for many years to come. 

David is an Assistant Principal at an alternative high school, and I am a Statistician, doing research in sea-level change.  We love to enjoy the amazing food and culture in Brooklyn and elsewhere, so we have taken advantage of the possibility of subsidizing a bit of our travel by putting our home on Airbnb while we are away having our own adventures.

Last summer we traveled around the Western US in our camper trailer exploring the national parks, hiking and working remotely, turning COVID into an opportunity for more exploration.

Christie was out of town, but co-host Jackie made sure we were checked in and was available to answer questions. Christian even checked in with us later in our stay to see how things were going. The place is by a lot of restaurants and bars. It's also not far from the subway station. I would recommend this place to anyone and would love to use the space again.

name: Beautiful, Sunny Victorian, 30 mins to Midtown NYC

reviews.comments:
We enjoyed Kirsten’s home for our family’s Christmas celebration. The house was large and welcoming which included an office for my son to work from!
Bedrooms were large with wonderful linens and comfy mattresses. The half bath on the first floor was great for us seniors who didn’t want to navigate stairs several times a day (the kids didn’t mind). They are athletes and enjoyed runs in Tibbets Park.
It was a great location for east access to the city as well as to visit other family members in the area.
Up the street within walking distance are a number of pubs and restaurants. By car literally 10 minutes away were even more great places to eat. Do yourself a favor and try Louie and Johnny on Yonkers Ave. for great Italian! For the best pizza you can’t beat Raceway Pizza.

Kirsten is a great communicator and always responded within a few minutes. Her placed was very clean and we had a great Thanksgiving in NYC.  If staying in NYC I would recommend Kirsten's place. Access to mid town is a train ride away !!

Kirsten’s house was exactly what we were looking for! With an extremely close proximity to manhattan, and easily accessible from the highway, the beautiful house was perfection. There were 4 full bedrooms with comfortable beds and thoughtful details throughout. The living room was a delight to rest after a day of work, to have a cocktail or play board games, and the backyard, with its firepit, is so inviting! We will definitely be back, and thank you so much to Kirsten for letting us stay in her beautiful space!!

Was very easy and quick to communicate with Kirsten, she was always polite and quickly reply my messages to answer questions or requests. The house was exactly how is posted, nice location (we were driving, was very close to the highway, very convenient), clean space, extra towels, amenities, nice heat in every room of the house and the house was huge and beautiful!! Have a cute backyard where I sat to read in the mornings and nice decorations. Even a guide book with every single detail you need to know. You can see she spend time putting all the peaces together.
Is located in a peaceful and quiet area, which make it perfect for a lil getaway relaxing time no far from the city.
Aww to be honest, I enjoyed my stay so much, I would totally recommend to other guests. Thank you for everything Kirsten!! :)
It’s a great location, but it was hot on the 3rd floor. Overall it was a nice stay ! Loved the whole vibe of the house.

Kirsten's home felt just like that: homey. It was lovely and comfortable and cared for with personal touches throughout: plants, books, art and artifacts, etc. The house is old but well kept. The third floor bedrooms got hot because of the summer weather, but sleeping was possible because of the fans provided. Second floor bedrooms have air conditioners. Living room was super comfortable. Yonkers itself didn't have a lot to do and Manhattan was about an hour away by subway on Saturday night. Overall, a really good value if you don't mind the travel time downtown.
Wonderful host with a wonderful place, highly recommend!

Such a LOVELY home!!! It's beautiful and has such a nice lovely spirit amongst its three floors, four bedrooms. The house has the charm of an old house but really thoughtfully maintained. Everything was so clean and easy, including generous use of kitchen items, towels and linens. The host Kirsten was so responsive and great.

And a super little backyard out behind the house.

Couldn't have been better!!
Charming colonial home in Yonkers. Historic details that made us feel back in time! Lovely host. Thanks for a great trip!
Beautiful home! Great communication! Great location! Enjoyed our stay!

We had a good time at Green Gables, a perfect location for attending a family wedding at the New York Botanical Garden combined with doing some touristy things in NYC and the Bronx Zoo (we drove everywhere, parking was easy on street near the house). Big spacious rooms, and we also enjoyed the fire pit in the backyard. We stayed with our three children, ages 1, 3, and 5, and were a bit worried about damaging some of the beautiful furniture and glass pieces in the house, but all emerged unscathed! Well stocked kitchen but be aware there is no dishwasher. Great washer and dryer, great water pressure in shower, comfortable beds, and a big comfortable couch to relax on at the end of the day, and a really well stocked office space with printer. Kirsten was very quick to respond with any questions, and was really accommodating with check in and check out times. The house is older with great character. Thank you!
Beautiful space for a little artist getaway. Thank you for hosting us!

name: Royal Suite @ Northern Lights Mansion

reviews.comments: I had high hopes for this inn but it is in serious disrepair. Many basic fixtures, outlets and plumbing, haven’t been attended to in what seem like years. I had to move to a downstairs room because the upstairs was sweltering; the new room was filthy and had a broken outlet. I had to charge my phone and dry hair using an extension cord on the floor. The shower door seal is decayed and so the bathroom floor got all wet every shower. The only amenity is a dirty bottle of Head and Shoulders shampoo because I guess we all have dandruff? The linens are washed with industrial soap and smell horrible. The hot tub clearly hadn’t been serviced and barely functioned. The toilet moaned after every flush. The female innkeeper did change the sheets and tidy it up but the room still felt grimy and there was no housekeeping during the stay. Another innkeeper was always around me to the point that as a woman I felt very uncomfortable and borderline unsafe. The bed was comfortable, thank goodness.
reviews.response:
Dear Erika,
Thank you for your review, we will update our maintainance items you listed. But I really think most of the items can be easily solved if you or staffs call me directly. The windows have upper panels you can slide down and will allow the cooler the air in the room immediately. Because you booked the most beautiful room upstairs. The room details did not include jacuzzi, if you would really like to book the room with the Jacuzzi, we only have two but most amazing water fall Jacuzzi units. This suite is not one of them. About the outlets, there are many outlets and every sides of the walls, you probably didn't see them, you can ask the staffs to point out for you. Our male staff has been with us for more than 3-4 yrs, he probably cares for your comfort, if he made you feel uncomfortable, I apologize, if he is trying to be too friendly, I will let him know and be more professional. We wish you very Happy Holidays and thank you for writing a review for us. Regards,
NLM

We could have shared with you more about the numerous passions and hidden talents of our host but it will be better for you to discover them by yourselves.
reviews.response: The Andersons are so wonderful we feel like having our family here. Such a lovely family and fun to share many stories at the dining table. Happy New Year 2022 & Wish you and family Healthy & Happy Journeys always...XOXOXO.

reviews.comments:

and downstairs area. Very friendly hosts, upon our stay they went above and beyond. reviews.response: Thank you so much for your patience. We are very happy to able to host you at the room you planned. We hope to see you again sometimes. Happy New Year Adam !.

reviews.comments:

It was a cheaper room and when I pointed out that I had paid for the more expensive room, it was agreed that I would be refunded for the cost of one night because of the inconvenience.
However, this has not happened yet. When I emailed the host to ask about it, I didn’t get any response.
So overall, a nice spot. A little noisy with other guests up and down the stairs if it’s a full house.
Disappointed that at this point I have overpaid for what I got and the host doesn’t seem super concerned about sticking to her word on the refund.

We had 2 friends come visit overnight the first night, and Oscar was completely accommodating with that, as well as our late checkout on New Year’s Day. He is very responsive with communicating, and gives clear instructions and responses. The place is maybe a 4 minute walk from the Junction Ave. 7 train station, and that close to the Q72 bus station. The neighborhood felt very safe, and we enjoyed the ethnicity of it. We leave a 10/10 recommendation, and will remember it in the event we return to NYC.

Our stay with friends and family couldn’t have been any better. We loved the place and Oscar was an excellent host and timely with responses on questions I had. I loved how close the train station was and many spots to eat and check out. Overall I will definitely be returning and recommending this home. Just the perfect fit.
Nice space for large group of people. Prefect for reunions!

5 STARS!! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

My family stayed here for my wedding while visiting. The location was incredible and made everyone fall in love with QUEENS! Very spacious for a big family and convenient to get around anywhere. Can’t beat the proximity to nearby shops. This is a must-stay for a great Queens experience. Everything was solid.
Super clean, plenty of space for a family of five, convenient to the subway, and quiet. Really enjoyed our stay and would go there again.
It’s a great place to live in. Super big and clean. Oscar was very nice and helped us a lot! We really appreciate it.

First time in this part of NYC and where in town for some shows at Citi Field. The location was very walkable to Citi Field and the walk both during the day and at night was safe. The area, depending on where you are from, might give you some concerns but we found it to be fun.

The location was good, with lots of surrounding places to grab snacks and a bite to eat. The place was clean, but would be a challenge with more than 4-6 people given size of the two bathrooms and limited common space.

We had one issue with hot water but Oscar resolved it within a day.
The place is great. It’s huge and super clean. Oscar was easy to reach. Everyone enjoyed the stay.

Parking on the street was hard to find but Oscar provided us a parking spot for a extra fee which was cool. Loved this place, If I’m ever back in New York this is where I’ll be staying!

My daughter and I were very happy with the cable TV. The room has an en suite bathroom.I really appreciated this - you can avoid running down the hall in a towel while clutching your toiletries.

While I only met Gordon on my last day (this was over the holidays), I felt that if I had a problem I would hear from him quickly. The photos of music superstars and music awards were interesting to see as well. There are many restaurants just around the corner on Myrtle Avenue, with a Walgreen's nearby and numerous delis. A few blocks away there are some verrrrry good restaurants and some nice little stores. The privacy and quiet of the place was very restorative!

Beautiful brownstone in prime neighborhood. It was very cozy and I had the pleasure to meet the host Gordon. He was very helpful and has an incredibly warm spirit. This was a great stay.  The train is a bit of a hike but I would definitely stay here again!

Gordon is an excellent host, and I always felt welcomed by his warm and genuine personality.  His home is a beautiful gem in Brooklyn nestled in a quiet neighborhood within walking distance to lots of different places to check out during your stay.  Fort Greene is a nice park to walk through which is close by.  Highly recommend staying here.  You won't be disappointed.
Gordon's place is in a perfect neighborhood, perfectly clean and he's the perfect host.
We felt welcomed; the room was exactly as pictured with a comfortable bed; neighborhood was convenient for our family; we hope to stay there again.
Gordon is a wonderful and welcoming  host.  Location is perfect as our son attends Pratt and kicking around Brooklyn was great.  We hope to visit and stay again in the future.

Gordon was very friendly and his place was very comfortable and beautiful. The location was great on a tree-lined street in a little community that had a great feel to it. Super interesting looking at all Gordon's awards and achievements in the music industry.

N/a
Beautiful Home, lovely decor definitely great for large families. Easy process as far as check-in, check-out and the rules are reasonable. Thanks again!

There were good and bad things about staying at Mark's place.

The good things: the apartment is very clean (except for a problem with the trash cans - see below), the beds are comfortable, the sheets don't smell strongly of laundry detergent, the neighborhood is quiet at night and although it at first seemed kind of sketchy was perfectly safe and we ended up liking it, the location is perfect for what we needed, there was parking.

The bad things: the address was WRONG on the Airbnb landing page for the apartment, so I went to the wrong address. I find this unimaginable and was a very bad start. Made me think the place was not real and a scam. I called the listing manager in a panic, and she said she had messaged me the correct address, but messages is not where I would naturally look for an address. I look at the landing page for the listing. I took another LYFT and found the address. The apartment is on the bottom floor, has next to no natural light, and feels like a cave. It feels a bit like a low level corporate hotel. There is no access to the backyard although it is right there. There were no lids on the trash cans in the kitchen and there was a fruit fly problem. When we took out the trash, there were no replacement liners. There was also no dish soap. We had to buy some. When we asked for liners, someone came into the apartment when we weren't there without alerting us to drop them off. It was hot and humid when we were there, and we had a hard time managing the AC. It was programmed by someone's phone, and the heat kept turning on, which makes no sense in the summer. We could not manage it ourselves, and we had a hard time with how hot it kept getting. The building manager turned off the water 3 times when we were at the apartment working during the day. He tried to do it again the next day, and I had to insist that he didn't do that while we were there. The place is extremely sterile and feels plastic and cheap except for a few nice armchairs in rooms. The sheets and bedding are all synthetic. All of the pots and pans are cheap, scratched up and ruined teflon, so do not plan to cook there. All together it wasn't a good experience (although there were a few redeeming quantities), and we would not stay there again.

Located just beyond the lobby of Hotel 32|32 is Sushi By Bou Nomad, one of the most revolutionary sushi concepts to take New York by storm in the last several years. Sushi By Bou Nomad specializes in Japanese style Omakase, also known as a “chefs choice” sushi tasting. Delicate and fresh fish is served in a sleek and comfortable setting, all within a 30 minute time period, making Sushi By Bou Nomad perfect for a quick lunch, or pre/post theater dinner. Just past Sushi By Bou is Lost Hours, a project by the acclaimed cocktail team of Death and Company, one of America’s top cocktail institutions. With a laid back and sophisticated vibe, Lost Hours blends beautiful Japanese inspired cocktails, with small bites that complement the drinks perfectly.

Hello to anyone who is looking through reviews to assure you are doing your due diligence in reserving the right place for your trip! I am here to ease your mind!

This apartment is located in a very "real" neighborhood in Brooklyn. What we love so much about this place is that it hasn't yet been gentrified and robbed of its culture like most of the other areas in Brooklyn which have pushed locals out of their homes and grown stale and predictable with the whitewashing of spaces.

Please pay attention that the issue was not actually with location, as noted, it is a close walk to the 2/3 train as well as the A/C train. The issue for some is with "location" in terms of a culture of people and how that culture takes space in their own neighborhoods.

So, to reiterate, this is an authentic Brooklyn neighborhood with a very rich and delightful black community! Yes there is a dog park a stones throw away, your local coffee shops, and museums, but this is also one of the few neighborhoods that still feels like proper NY with real communities of people who have been here for generations.
If being in a predominately black neighborhood or being immersed in black culture on your walks to the subway or coffee shop makes you feel uncomfortable, perhaps try booking in a more gentrified neighborhood.

If anyone has questions feel free to message!

We were looking forward to staying in Brooklyn, but unfortunately we didn't have a great experience at this AirBnb. The place is very nicely decorated as shown in the pictures, but not very comfortable. When we arrived it was swelteringly hot (we stayed in August). Once we turned on the AC units it started to cool down except for one bedroom unit. We informed Michelle of this issue and her response was that the unit was working fine and we should clean the filter. My husband was able to get the unit working by cycling it, but it took a while and made for an unpleasant night, especially because the mattress in that bedroom is not comfortable at all. I'm not sure even how to describe it, but it was more like a futon stuffed with plastic. My husband described it as "sleeping on a bunch of diapers." We also had issues with the water. It was either scaldingly hot in the downstairs bedroom or not hot at all in the upstairs bathroom. Please be advised if you have any mobility issues as all three bedrooms require you to walk up or down a set of narrow stairs. Michelle was not friendly to deal with. We requested early check-in when we booked the AirBnb and she could not tell me if she would be able to accommodate that request until 2 hrs before we checked in. Ultimately she let us check in 1 hr early. No flexibility with check-out. The location is pretty good, and easy walking distance to lots of restaurants. We recommend Luigi's for pizza and Al-Noor Halal Deli for Mediterranean food. Brooklyn is great, and we were hoping to have a more authentic experience by staying in an AirBnb, but now we wished we had just stayed at a hotel.

primaryHost.about:
Welcome to The Knickerbocker, the first luxury hotel in Times Square. Edging the bright lights of Broadway and the calm of Bryant Park, it is a legendary New York landmark reborn. Enjoy the ultimate New Year's Eve experience atop Times Square at the St. Cloud Rooftop.

Conceived as the premier luxury lifestyle hotel overlooking Times Square between Broadway and Bryant Park, The Knickerbocker’s 330 guestrooms, including 27 Junior Suites and 4 Tribute Suites—the Caruso, Cohan, Martini and Parrish—offer the perfect respite from the high-octane energy of a vibrant city. Nestled within the hotel’s 16-story Beaux-Art façade, all accommodations boast a sleek and contemporary style, with customized floorplans, soaring 12-foot ceilings, 8-foot doors and 6-foot windows creating an indulgent sense of space. Bespoke furnishings, oak wood finishes, richly textured fabrics and intelligent lighting add to the sublime ambiance, while plush Stearns & Foster® Euro-top beds piled high with luxurious SFERRA® linens and Ploh® feather pillows invite blissful moments of calm and reprieve. Whether traveling for business or pleasure, guests staying in The Knickerbocker’s New York City suites will find all the comforts of home at their fingertips, from state-of-the-art technologies to exclusive dyptique bath amenities.

Please be advised, Jakes Cafe, in room dining and minibar have been temporarily supended.  Alternatively, it would be our pleasure to direct you our restaurant Charlie Palmer for Full Breakfast Buffet daily from 7a-11am. In addition, our rooftop bar, St. Cloud is available for light bites and cocktails from 4p-11pm Tues-Sat.

Should you have additional questions regarding our current services and amenities, we encourage you to contact us. We look forward to welcoming you.

Our selected accommodations combine the best features of a hotel and vacation rental home to ensure a wonderful and effortless stay! We take the guesswork out of where you are staying so you can concentrate on what you want to be doing.

We handpick the accommodations in the best properties all over the US offering great vacation rental experience and impeccable service: serviced apartments, oversized suites and accommodations in resorts with outstanding amenities and much more! We do this by testing them ourselves before the hit the list, so we know what to expect before you make the reservation. 

We are available 24/7 to make sure all your special requests are taken care of and to assist with any questions or issues you might have throughout your stay!
